The paper discusses an automated tool for debugging difficult bugs in complex, real-world multithreaded programs, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The tool is based on a reversible debugger and a binary search algorithm, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of checkpoint-restart and deterministic record-replay plugins suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of multi-core architectures during replay, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on debugging and bug diagnosis could also suggest that it belongs to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category.
